text: Rostock (German pronunciation: [ˈʁɔstɔk]) is a city in the northeast of Germany. It is in the state of Mecklenburg-Western Pomerania. Rostock has over 200,000 people (204,260 in December 2011). It has an old university (founded in 1419). The town is on the river Warnow. The mayor is Roland Methling. The city today has the name Hansestadt (Hanseatic city) in memory of its history, where it has been an important part of the Hanseatic League. The architecture of the city and the region is influenced by this historic period. Rostock is on the Baltic Sea. It has an important harbor. A district of the city, Warnemünde, is famous for its long beaches. It has a humid continental climate (Dfb in the Koeppen climate classification). The most important football club of Rostock is F.C. Hansa Rostock. It is in the German Bundesliga. Other major Hanseatic cities today are: Hamburg, Lübeck, Wismar, Stralsund, Bremen, Greifswald and Demmin. == References == ==Other websites== Category:Port cities and towns of the Baltic Sea Category:Ports and harbours of Germany Category:Urban districts of Mecklenburg-Western Pomerania Category:13th- century establishments in Germany Category:1210s establishments in Europe
